      <p class="eyebrow">Support</p>
      <h1>Cashora Support</h1>
      <p>Cashora Budget Tracking is built to help you manage income, expenses, budgets, and a manual investment portfolio in a simple way. The sections below cover the most common support topics.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Support email: <a href="mailto:hello@neondustlabs.com">hello@neondustlabs.com</a></p>
      <p>Please include your iOS version, Cashora version, and a short description of the issue.</p>

      <h2>Where is my data stored?</h2>
      <p>Cashora Budget Tracking is local-first. Your transaction and investment records are stored on your device. This version does not include live market APIs, broker connections, or third-party analytics SDKs.</p>

      <h2>How can I delete my data?</h2>
      <p>You can use the "Delete All Data" option in Settings to remove transactions, investment assets, custom categories, and related local preferences. This action cannot be undone.</p>

      <h2>How does export work?</h2>
      <p>CSV and PDF exports are started by the user. When the share sheet opens, the user chooses which app or service to share the file with.</p>

      <h2>Face ID / Touch ID</h2>
      <p>The app lock uses Apple's LocalAuthentication framework. Cashora Budget Tracking does not see, store, or share biometric data.</p>

      <h2>About the investment screen</h2>
      <p>The investment screen is only for manual portfolio tracking. Cashora Budget Tracking does not provide trading, investment advice, broker connections, or real-time market data.</p>
